URL: https://github.com/ciccalab/Kandinsky
Description: 'Kandinsky' is a spatial analysis toolkit designed to provide a compendium of methods to study cell and spot spatial neighbourhoods using spatial transcriptomic and proteomic data. 'Kandinsky' is compatible with most of the commercially available spatial transcriptomics and proteomics technologies, and it can be used with any data type providing cell or spot information (including spatial coordinates) in a tabular format.
